resources.string:
This test verifies that the Nfc-A and ISO-DEP protocol parameters are being set correctly. The test may be passed when no FAIL entries show up in the results below. Note that the reader device may be different from the device under test - the DUT itself does not need to be able to act as the reader for this test. 

 Note that for each test there are 3 possible outcomes:
1) OK -> test has passed;
2) FAIL -> test has failed and this must be fixed;
3) FAIL EMVCO -> this protocol parameter is deviating from the requirements in the EMV Contactless Communication Protocol specification.

While it is allowed to ship a HCE implementation with EMVCo failures, it may not perform optimal when EMVco based payment HCE apps are run on the device.
